<font color="#FF0000">THE NURSES OF VIET NAM</font><br>
<tt>Tue Dec  3  2:13:02 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
At the Air Base in Danang in August of 1968, I came in on a 130 from Phu Bai with a dozen or so other walking wounded types.  Somehow I ended up at the small little aid station on the northwest side of the field...dirty, smelling like 40 miles of bad road, and bloody and mad.  Around 10:00 P.M. (2200 for those of you still into it)You came into the ward where I was the only patient, with a tray of the best hamburgers I have ever had.  Semper Fi, darling, you have been loved every day of my life since then.
